## Mong Chart Box Runtime Rule

- Graph-only guide screens constrain Pattie/Mong to the chart box and use a deterministic bar-to-bar `jump`/`climb` sequence instead of free roaming.
- Test sprite generation normalizes each frame's alpha bounds to a shared center line and bottom line before building sprite sheets.
- Weekly sales chart NPC movement uses a chart-local absolute coordinate system. Valid terrain surfaces are the chart floor and each bar's top surface, calculated from `getBoundingClientRect()`.
- Upward movement selects `jump` or `climb`; downward movement uses `hopDown` with a small arc. The NPC must never target arbitrary points outside chart terrain surfaces.
- Chart NPC initial placement must use the chart floor surface, not bar top surfaces, because bar height animation may still be at 0% on first render.
- Walk/run tuning must adjust both coordinate duration and sprite frame duration so the pet does not visually slide.
- Chart NPC platform coordinates must be chart-local (`offsetLeft`/`offsetTop` accumulated to the chart root), not viewport coordinates, to avoid jitter during Excel sheet scrolling.
- Chart NPC initialization must wait until the management sheet is visible and the chart has non-zero dimensions; hidden-sheet initialization can leave the sprite at `translate(0, 0)`.
- For browser-visible UI movement bugs, verify with headless browser tab switching and DOM coordinate snapshots before finalizing.


