## Production Corgi Asset Loader Rule

- Production Mong/Corgi sprite sheet originals live in `manually_command/export`.
- The source sprite sheets are Aseprite exports with 1px padding and must not be edited.
- Runtime static copies live in `public/assets/corgi/` and are referenced through `public/assets/corgi/manifest.json`.
- Frame counts differ by animation and must be inferred from actual image dimensions.
- Sprite slicing must account for source padding/spacing; fix code when image structure and code assumptions conflict.
